  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food Assistance to the most vulnerable people affected by COVID-19 in the northeast Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving food security assistance to vulnerable communities in Borno and Yobe states. This WFP project provides voucher assistance to 90,552 people, including 32,000 women, 23,000 men, and over 35,000 children. This project is part of an $80 million CERF allocation to support cash programming in response to increasing food insecurity in 6 countries.</narrative>
  </description>
